::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:45.590 --> 00:01:53.160
Going back in time a bit, we find Zoro, who has
recently been sent to the same island as Perona...

3
00:01:45.960 --> 00:01:48.960
Ruins of the Muggy Kingdom
Gloom Island

4
00:01:57.300 --> 00:01:58.540
Is this...

5
00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:01.110
...a tomb?

6
00:02:01.110 --> 00:02:02.940
Who made this?!

7
00:02:03.470 --> 00:02:05.840
It was carved from a massive tree.

8
00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:08.050
Such incredible craftsmanship...

9
00:02:08.050 --> 00:02:10.650
This thing is huge!

10
00:02:21.590 --> 00:02:22.490
So fast!

11
00:02:40.140 --> 00:02:42.510
What?! It got deflected!

12
00:02:42.950 --> 00:02:44.780
H-Hey! Look!

13
00:02:59.330 --> 00:03:01.500
You bastards!

14
00:03:15.650 --> 00:03:20.480
The Land of Poverty, Hungeria
Lazy Bones Island

15
00:03:16.450 --> 00:03:20.480
Meanwhile, on Lazy Bones Island
in the impoverished nation of Hungeria...

16
00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:24.990
Brook was mistaken as 
the Dark Lord, Satan, by its residents.

17
00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:38.100
What a bright and beautiful morning!

18
00:03:43.610 --> 00:03:45.710
It's the longarms!

19
00:03:44.980 --> 00:03:45.710
Huh?

20
00:03:54.120 --> 00:03:54.950
No!

21
00:03:54.950 --> 00:03:55.990
Help me!

22
00:03:57.990 --> 00:04:00.590
Do you wanna get hurt?!

23
00:04:00.590 --> 00:04:01.990
Return that girl!

24
00:04:02.690 --> 00:04:04.900
Quit messing with us, you bastards!

25
00:04:04.900 --> 00:04:06.700
Let my daughter go!

26
00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:10.230
We'll send you straight to hell!

27
00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:16.140
Huh?!

28
00:04:16.140 --> 00:04:17.640
No!

29
00:04:17.640 --> 00:04:19.640
Help me!

30
00:04:20.580 --> 00:04:23.210
You know they're abducting that young lady, right?

31
00:04:23.210 --> 00:04:24.310
Yes!

32
00:04:24.310 --> 00:04:26.220
Hurry up and hex them!

33
00:04:26.220 --> 00:04:27.680
I beg you!

34
00:04:29.420 --> 00:04:31.720
That's not– We need to save her! Now!

35
00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:34.490
Lord Satan!

36
00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:39.560
They took her...

37
00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:41.270
Lord Satan!

38
00:04:42.230 --> 00:04:44.030
I beseech you!

39
00:04:44.030 --> 00:04:46.500
Please bring your wrath down upon them!

40
00:04:46.500 --> 00:04:48.470
– We beseech you!
– We beseech you!

41
00:04:50.570 --> 00:04:54.340
They're really dependent on other people!

42
00:04:56.810 --> 00:04:59.880
But that young lady is a victim!

43
00:04:59.880 --> 00:05:01.590
She doesn't deserve this!

44
00:05:02.450 --> 00:05:03.550
All right!

45
00:05:03.550 --> 00:05:07.930
I'll do it since I owe you for all the food...
Not to mention all the panties!

46
00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:11.300
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

47
00:05:12.330 --> 00:05:13.900
– Satan!
– Satan!

48
00:05:14.360 --> 00:05:17.940
– Satan! Satan!
– Satan! Satan!

49
00:05:17.940 --> 00:05:21.610
– Satan! Satan!
– Satan! Satan!

50
00:05:21.610 --> 00:05:23.870
Luffy. Everyone!

51
00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:29.510
Right now, I have become Satan,
surrounded by panties.

52
00:05:29.510 --> 00:05:32.250
My apologies, but...
could you wait a little longer?

53
00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:36.120
I owe them a debt, and running off
without repaying it would be spineless!

54
00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:38.220
So please, excuse my absence.

55
00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:41.790
As soon as I complete this single task,
I'll be back by your side!

56
00:05:51.030 --> 00:05:57.110
This is the Birdie Kingdom, in the South Blue,
where birds reign supreme.

57
00:05:53.100 --> 00:05:57.110
Birdie Kingdom
South Blue

58
00:06:09.090 --> 00:06:12.090
I really wanna get off this island.

59
00:06:12.860 --> 00:06:15.460
This place is the worst.

60
00:06:16.730 --> 00:06:19.400
The birds treat me like a toy.

61
00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:24.270
The humans want to add me to their hot pot.

62
00:06:26.170 --> 00:06:27.940
And what's more...

63
00:06:27.940 --> 00:06:29.570
the birds and the humans...

64
00:06:31.540 --> 00:06:34.280
are always fighting.

65
00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:41.320
What should I do?

66
00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:59.440
This is the Kamabakka Queendom
on Peachy Island, in the Grand Line.

67
00:06:55.670 --> 00:06:59.440
Kamabakka Queendom
Peachy Island, Grand Line

68
00:07:03.270 --> 00:07:05.240
What is this place?!

69
00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:06.940
More importantly…

70
00:07:07.950 --> 00:07:10.080
what's with these people?!

71
00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:27.100
Damn!

72
00:07:27.100 --> 00:07:28.730
I've been waiting for you!

73
00:07:39.810 --> 00:07:41.710
Wh-Who are you?!

74
00:07:52.360 --> 00:07:55.930
Dear Nami, Robin,

75
00:07:55.930 --> 00:07:57.360
how are you both doing?

76
00:07:58.030 --> 00:08:01.230
I'm looking forward to seeing you two!

77
00:08:02.770 --> 00:08:07.440
When the time comes, I'm sure
that we'll become good friends!

78
00:08:25.560 --> 00:08:33.000
This is the small sky island of Weatheria,
home to scientists who study the weather.

79
00:08:35.930 --> 00:08:38.940
Weatheria

80
00:08:38.940 --> 00:08:40.540
Young lady!

81
00:08:41.240 --> 00:08:42.940
Over here!

82
00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:45.040
A ship?!

83
00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:50.750
Whoa! What's with this ship? It floats?!

84
00:08:55.320 --> 00:08:57.590
Nooo!

85
00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:01.430
Let's go!

86
00:09:01.860 --> 00:09:03.090
What?!

87
00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:16.340
This island is exactly what I was looking for!

88
00:09:19.940 --> 00:09:21.340
This island?

89
00:09:25.680 --> 00:09:29.150
You can save our island?!

90
00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:30.490
Yes.

91
00:09:30.490 --> 00:09:35.290
Just watch me use
weather science to make it rain!

92
00:09:35.290 --> 00:09:36.630
What did you just say?!

93
00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.500
Why, I could do it right now,
for the special price...

94
00:09:41.970 --> 00:09:44.530
of 100 million belly!

95
00:09:44.530 --> 00:09:45.240
100 million?!

96
00:09:49.740 --> 00:09:51.410
Do you think that's a bit too much?

97
00:09:51.410 --> 00:09:54.340
That's way too much! No one can afford that!

98
00:09:56.910 --> 00:09:58.680
Is that so...?

99
00:09:58.680 --> 00:10:01.020
Alright, then let's make it 100 belly!

100
00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:01.020
Huh?!

101
00:10:01.490 --> 00:10:02.650
– What a deal!
– What a deal!

102
00:10:11.030 --> 00:10:12.200
Are those...

103
00:10:13.760 --> 00:10:15.370
soap bubbles?

104
00:10:16.570 --> 00:10:18.640
There's something inside.

105
00:10:20.240 --> 00:10:24.110
Young lady, could you generate
some wind with this?

106
00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:27.940
Oh, this is...

107
00:10:28.980 --> 00:10:30.710
Do you want it at full power?

108
00:10:30.710 --> 00:10:32.380
Yes!

109
00:11:00.940 --> 00:11:03.410
I can't believe this!

110
00:11:23.170 --> 00:11:24.330
It's raining!

111
00:11:38.880 --> 00:11:40.520
We did it!

112
00:11:44.990 --> 00:11:46.790
They sure seem happy.

113
00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:47.820
Yeah!

114
00:11:47.820 --> 00:11:50.690
Now, don't you think that
weather science is useful?

115
00:12:01.570 --> 00:12:07.080
Meanwhile, on Mech Island, Futureland: Baldimore,
the birthplace of a certain genius...

116
00:12:05.840 --> 00:12:09.250
Mech Island
Futureland Baldimore

117
00:12:12.780 --> 00:12:14.580
Let's get him to the hospital, Kitton!

118
00:12:14.580 --> 00:12:15.590
Okay!

119
00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:38.170
Surgery in
Progress

120
00:12:38.810 --> 00:12:40.940
Ah, I see. He's a cyborg.

121
00:12:40.940 --> 00:12:42.980
To think his energy source is cola…

122
00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:44.750
What should we do?

123
00:12:44.750 --> 00:12:46.880
We don't have any cola here.

124
00:12:47.980 --> 00:12:50.650
There's no time to lose. Begin the operation.

125
00:12:50.650 --> 00:12:51.450
Understood.

126
00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:57.090
Surgery in
Progress

127
00:13:10.640 --> 00:13:11.840
Mister!

128
00:13:17.780 --> 00:13:20.780
Greetings! You're the young lad
from earlier, yes?

129
00:13:20.780 --> 00:13:23.350
My apologies for keeping you waiting!

130
00:13:25.490 --> 00:13:28.330
S-Something's different about you.

131
00:13:28.730 --> 00:13:32.030
Indeed! Sadly, they don't
have any cola here, so...

132
00:13:32.830 --> 00:13:35.070
they powered me up with tea instead.

133
00:13:35.070 --> 00:13:36.630
It's Darjeeling!

134
00:13:36.970 --> 00:13:37.700
Tea?

135
00:13:44.470 --> 00:13:47.340
What a super flavour!

136
00:13:52.180 --> 00:13:54.350
Now I feel super relaxed!

137
00:13:55.190 --> 00:13:56.920
M-Mister!

138
00:13:57.650 --> 00:13:59.360
Oh! How thoughtless of me!

139
00:14:03.160 --> 00:14:05.830
There you are! Careful now, it's piping hot.

140
00:14:13.740 --> 00:14:16.170
No, no! That's not what I was gonna say!

141
00:14:16.610 --> 00:14:20.110
Mister! You were funnier before, and I miss it!

142
00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:21.910
Oh, truly?

143
00:14:46.700 --> 00:14:47.900
So cold!

144
00:14:49.540 --> 00:14:51.940
How did I get here?

145
00:14:54.280 --> 00:14:56.610
Splendid, a scarf!

146
00:14:57.650 --> 00:14:58.410
Oh?

147
00:15:08.220 --> 00:15:10.660
What is going on here?!

148
00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:16.230
"Keep out"?

149
00:15:16.230 --> 00:15:19.740
"This forest is a mecha-animal enclosure."

150
00:15:50.730 --> 00:15:53.340
Operation: Surprise Jungle Awakening!

151
00:15:54.340 --> 00:15:59.010
Survive and regain the wildness
in your heart, Mister!

152
00:15:59.010 --> 00:16:02.250
Now, now, let's all calm down.

153
00:16:02.850 --> 00:16:04.750
You all seem quite irritated.

154
00:16:04.750 --> 00:16:06.720
Have you not eaten breakfast yet?

155
00:16:06.720 --> 00:16:11.350
Your disposition will suffer
if you don't eat properly!

156
00:16:13.420 --> 00:16:14.890
Ah, I see!

157
00:16:14.890 --> 00:16:17.860
This is breakfast time!

158
00:16:17.860 --> 00:16:19.700
What was I thinking?

159
00:16:24.630 --> 00:16:26.070
Dee-licious!

160
00:16:26.070 --> 00:16:28.940
Nothing quite like the first
cup of tea in the morning!

161
00:16:37.310 --> 00:16:40.020
It feels great to be alive!

162
00:16:40.850 --> 00:16:42.290
It's not working!

163
00:17:10.380 --> 00:17:12.980
Help us!

164
00:17:16.690 --> 00:17:18.050
Violence is not–

165
00:17:20.290 --> 00:17:22.790
I know you're at the age where you want to act–

166
00:17:24.290 --> 00:17:25.090
If you let me–

167
00:17:26.100 --> 00:17:26.700
You'll see–

168
00:17:27.260 --> 00:17:28.630
Let's sort this out...

169
00:17:29.730 --> 00:17:30.900
in a civilized manner!

170
00:17:32.100 --> 00:17:36.070
Stop...! Nothing good...
comes... from violence!

171
00:17:36.810 --> 00:17:38.610
Mr. Frank!

172
00:17:38.610 --> 00:17:41.640
Oh no, it's not working at all!

173
00:17:41.640 --> 00:17:42.480
Relax–

174
00:17:43.550 --> 00:17:44.380
Listen to what I–

175
00:17:45.050 --> 00:17:46.120
Listen to what–

176
00:17:46.880 --> 00:17:47.920
Listen to–

177
00:17:48.650 --> 00:17:49.150
Listen–

178
00:17:51.350 --> 00:17:51.850
Lis–

179
00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:54.360
To–

180
00:17:55.460 --> 00:17:55.960
Listen–

181
00:17:56.730 --> 00:17:57.160
Lis–

182
00:17:57.890 --> 00:17:58.230
Li–

183
00:18:00.900 --> 00:18:02.170
Lis...

184
00:18:17.510 --> 00:18:20.850
Super!

185
00:18:27.790 --> 00:18:30.490
Who the hell do you think I am?!

186
00:18:30.490 --> 00:18:33.360
I am the Franky!

187
00:18:33.360 --> 00:18:35.000
Yeah!

188
00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:36.600
You're back, Mister!

189
00:18:37.100 --> 00:18:39.770
Per... vert!

190
00:18:41.840 --> 00:18:42.770
What's the matter?

191
00:18:44.170 --> 00:18:47.880
I got cooled down a little,
so I'm running out of steam!

192
00:18:47.880 --> 00:18:51.010
That's a pervert! I mean, problem!

193
00:18:51.010 --> 00:18:53.350
Um... Um...

194
00:18:53.350 --> 00:18:55.120
Oh, yeah! Let me show you something!

195
00:19:03.430 --> 00:19:10.030
Grandpa told me to keep away from here because
there are a lot of dangerous creations inside!

196
00:19:23.450 --> 00:19:29.450
Tequila Wolf
East Blue

197
00:19:30.720 --> 00:19:31.950
Here's your meal!

198
00:19:32.420 --> 00:19:35.460
Once you finish, your
interrogation will continue!

199
00:19:35.460 --> 00:19:36.990
Looking forward to it.

200
00:19:43.900 --> 00:19:47.670
Sounds like you've been
hurt badly, young lady.

201
00:19:47.670 --> 00:19:48.640
Who are you?

202
00:19:48.640 --> 00:19:50.910
I'm just an old man.

203
00:19:50.910 --> 00:19:53.890
I was sent to this country today,

204
00:19:53.890 --> 00:19:57.850
but they said the elderly are useless 
and put me in here.

205
00:19:58.250 --> 00:20:00.320
I'm sorry to hear that.

206
00:20:02.250 --> 00:20:03.220
What's that?!

207
00:20:06.520 --> 00:20:08.560
Dissidents are running wild!

208
00:20:11.290 --> 00:20:14.560
The warden ordered everyone
to go and break it up!

209
00:20:14.560 --> 00:20:15.430
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

210
00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:21.340
Dissidents?

211
00:20:21.340 --> 00:20:24.470
Yes, but as you ordered,

212
00:20:24.470 --> 00:20:27.740
all units were dispatched
to calm the situation!

213
00:20:29.210 --> 00:20:32.010
I didn't give that order.

214
00:20:32.720 --> 00:20:37.990
Don't tell me that you even sent
the guards stationed at the tower!

215
00:20:43.330 --> 00:20:46.100
I am an agent of the Revolutionary Army!

216
00:20:47.330 --> 00:20:48.660
Imbecile!

217
00:20:48.660 --> 00:20:51.030
I don't care about the dissidents!

218
00:20:51.030 --> 00:20:52.900
Don't let Nico Robin get away!

219
00:20:55.740 --> 00:20:56.870
Well done.

220
00:20:56.870 --> 00:20:59.740
Under your command, victory is assured.

221
00:20:59.740 --> 00:21:02.150
Worry not. You can count on me!

222
00:21:02.150 --> 00:21:05.950
While you're at it,
free that young woman, too.

223
00:21:12.290 --> 00:21:14.690
Shoot to kill!

224
00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:19.830
Clutch!

225
00:21:29.740 --> 00:21:31.840
You're Nico Robin?!

226
00:21:40.480 --> 00:21:43.390
Bowin Archipelago
Grand Line

227
00:21:43.990 --> 00:21:46.620
What the hell is this place?!

228
00:21:48.860 --> 00:21:50.860
That smells delicious!

229
00:21:50.860 --> 00:21:52.930
Oh yeah, these are definitely edible!

230
00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:54.830
Ramenfalls!

231
00:21:55.430 --> 00:21:56.800
Spaghetti patches!

232
00:21:57.400 --> 00:21:58.700
Hamfruit!

233
00:21:59.170 --> 00:22:01.040
And chocolate rocks for dessert!

234
00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:05.580
You can eat whatever you see!

235
00:22:06.410 --> 00:22:08.140
Oh, can I eat these?!

236
00:22:11.080 --> 00:22:11.980
Go ahead'n.

237
00:22:11.980 --> 00:22:12.620
Yum-yum!

238
00:22:13.050 --> 00:22:18.520
If you eat a lot and build your stamina,
then the man-eating plants won't attack you'n!

239
00:22:18.520 --> 00:22:20.390
Really? That's great!

240
00:22:20.390 --> 00:22:23.390
These are really good!
I could eat them forever!

241
00:22:23.390 --> 00:22:25.460
Don't just eat'n!

242
00:22:25.460 --> 00:22:27.060
You need to work out, too!

243
00:22:27.060 --> 00:22:28.500
I know!

244
00:22:28.500 --> 00:22:34.700
But I need to eat a lot to become
a cool hero of the forest like you, right?

245
00:22:41.580 --> 00:22:44.250
I can't eat another bite!

246
00:22:44.250 --> 00:22:45.650
Usopp'n...

247
00:22:46.150 --> 00:22:49.550
Fat things will surely be eaten on this island'n!

248
00:22:49.550 --> 00:22:51.390
Surely be eaten?!

249
00:22:51.790 --> 00:22:55.490
It is impossible to escape
from the Bowin Archipelago!

250
00:22:55.490 --> 00:22:57.490
Impossible to escape?!

251
00:22:57.860 --> 00:23:01.000
And I am the hero of the forest,

252
00:23:01.000 --> 00:23:01.430
H–
